              id: "2596008",
              plain_text: "Turning inland to the foothills of the Alps we wind through several ordinary towns inevitably layered in the rich history of conquest by the Romans, Greeks, Tuscans and others; past vineyards (some of them saved by California vines after disease struck vulnerable monocultures that had nearly decimated French viticulture) and into the flower–growing region of the Parfumeraries.",
