            created_at: 1455980447,
            text_fragment: {
              id: "2596013",
              plain_text: "We walked the tiny town from end–to–end and stem–to–stern several times, stopping to enjoy simple sandwiches and ice cream. The shops didn't do too much damage, sending us off with some linens, a silver heart, some honey and rose jam (that spoiled literally days after opening because of their adherence to principals of organic nonsense). \n\nWe began to get alarmed that there were no bathrooms in this place when we uncovered a pay toilet that proved to be a technological marvel with a mild intimidation factor. Since it only took exact change and we hadn't been using cash, the first trick was coming up with payment. Once inside, it is apparent the whole dank, cold and dripping room is sprayed with water and disinfectant between uses. Unfortunately it is not clear what triggers this action, so the unfamiliar user anxiously sits on the ice cold still wet stainless steel seat contemplating if they will make it out of this place dry, and agonizing over whether it is such a good idea to press the flush button! I picture that most users prepare for exit by edging as close to the door as possible, stretching out to trigger the button whilst leaping out of the target zone all in one motion (at least that was my approach). ",
              text_style: "body",
              modifiers: [],
              alignment: "left"
            },
