            updated_at: 1452836236,
            created_at: 1452836236,
            text_fragment: {
              id: "2502643",
              plain_text: "The Ponte Vecchio way, and the bridge itself, was lined with hi–end boutiques and gold and jewelry merchants — so overpriced that the ship's advisors and our guides warned us all to keep our wallets in our pockets for better deals elsewhere (and his commissions). Apparently most tourists got the same advice, the street was jammed with people posing and taking pictures of empty shops. We can confirm the prices were outrageous. Christoff, Gavin and I found this part of the tour interesting but overrated. Architecturally, not that great either, although it does illustrate how perceived value drove Italians to great lengths to build in improbable places and manners (note the accreted, crammed and clinging additions cantilevered and propped beyond the edge of the bridge).",
              text_style: "body",
              modifiers: [],
              alignment: "left"
            },
