            updated_at: 1452836236,
            created_at: 1452836236,
            text_fragment: {
              id: "2502646",
              plain_text: "We had ample time to explore and lunch while on the Piazza di Santa Croce, and also met up with mom and dad, who had taken a less rigorous tour.\n\nHere the commission the guides often earn paid off. First, Samuelé made sure we stopped in Gold Market, run by Maria, that easily captured NancyEllen's attention and a big chunk of our wallet. Second he and our parents highly recommended Boccadama. We were able to get a table in the overcrowded and popular place with no reservations because the proprietor reserves tables for Samuelé's group. Mamma Mia! What an amazing lunch! Cheap but good–tasting rustic chianti paired with the most delectable lasagna we'd ever had! We finished on the other side of the piazza with a gelato, before our tour of the inside of the church.",
              text_style: "body",
              modifiers: [],
              alignment: "left"
            },
