            created_at: 1452836205,
            text_fragment: {
              id: "2502628",
              plain_text: 'While cued up for our bus we spotted a wretched old crone painfully shuffling down the street with an outstretched gnarled hand in the clichéd "Alms for the poor" universal body language of beggars. Something seemed off—perhaps she was a little too perfectly bent, and picturesque, so we watched her slow progress with growing interest eventually realizing "she" was in fact a young man in costume playing a con on gullible tourist marks. Once he noticed our unwanted attention he skeddadled, suddenly quite spry, handing off his bag of spoils to his conspirator just as the next "old crone" emerged from an alley to take his place! Thus ended our day in Rome and the Vatican City.',
              text_style: "body",
              modifiers: [],
              alignment: "left"
            },
