            updated_at: 1452836112,
            created_at: 1452836112,
            text_fragment: {
              id: "2502570",
              plain_text: "While the Cathedral is modest in size, befitting such a tiny country, and quite beautiful, NancyEllen was particularly interested to see where Princess Grace, and Prince Rainier were laid to rest. We were all fascinated to find her stone in the floor festooned with flowers, notes and other offerings—while his was barren—confirming Michele's account of how beloved the American princess Grace was, in contrast to the native–son prince Rainier's well–earned legacy as a cad and a familial tyrant. He was probably jealous of the adoration showered on his American princess, which likely contributed to his malevolent treatment of her. Apparently he took after his forebear Francesco Grimaldi (translated from the Italian: The malicious one). ",
              text_style: "body",
              modifiers: [],
              alignment: "left"
            },
